<!-- 03 — TECHNOLOGY -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">What Makes ZLINE Different to Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">ZLINE isn't a European brand — it's an American company that took European design elements and applied US manufacturing economics. That creates specific service considerations.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Porcelain-Coated Cast Iron Grates</strong> — ZLINE ranges use cast iron grates with a fired porcelain enamel coating. This differs from bare cast iron (used on Wolf, Viking, Bertazzoni, BlueStar) in two service-relevant ways: porcelain chips at impact and cannot be re-seasoned, and coastal LA salt air accelerates rust formation wherever porcelain has chipped to expose bare iron. We inspect grate chip condition on every ZLINE range call and note where rust has initiated so the owner can address it proactively.</li>
        <li><strong>DuraSnow® Stainless</strong> — ZLINE's fingerprint-resistant stainless has a micro-textured surface that requires non-abrasive treatment during service. Standard stainless cleaning pads scratch DuraSnow®. We use only DuraSnow®-compatible cleaning agents and non-abrasive protective covers during all panel work. DuraSnow® surfaces also show scratches more readily than standard brushed stainless — one tool slip during careless service is immediately visible.</li>
        <li><strong>Sealed Burner Design</strong> — ZLINE professional ranges use sealed gas burners — the burner base is sealed to the cooktop to prevent spills entering the burner chamber. The sealed design requires specific igniter positioning. Generic igniters at incorrect geometry create weak spark even when new. We use OEM ZLINE igniters for correct spark gap alignment at each burner's BTU rating.</li>
        <li><strong>Dual-Fuel Configuration</strong> — ZLINE's dual-fuel ranges combine gas cooktop with electric oven — two independent systems. A power surge affecting both systems simultaneously looks like a mysterious multi-point failure but shares a common cause. We diagnose shared vs independent causes on every dual-fuel call before ordering parts for multiple components.</li>
        <li><strong>Range Hood CFM Ratings</strong> — ZLINE hoods range from 400 CFM to 1,200 CFM. The blower motor assembly is CFM-specific — a replacement motor must match the original CFM rating exactly, not just the physical dimensions. We identify the CFM spec before ordering any ZLINE hood motor. Installing the wrong CFM motor creates either inadequate ventilation or excessive noise.</li>
        <li><strong>Recall Awareness</strong> — As a 10-year-old brand that grew quickly, ZLINE has issued recalls on specific models for gas valve and igniter safety issues. We check recall status by model number as the first step of every ZLINE service call — before diagnosis, before any repair. An open recall may mean the repair is covered at no cost through ZLINE's service program.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#c8820a; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#e8a030">🌊 Coastal Porcelain Grate Rust</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">Coastal LA properties (within 5 miles of the ocean) see accelerated porcelain grate chip-to-rust progression. Salt air reaches the exposed cast iron within weeks once porcelain has chipped. A grate that shows minimal chip damage at inspection can have significant rust formation 3–4 months later. We document grate chip locations for coastal properties and recommend proactive replacement before rust spreads to the grate structure. Replacement ZLINE porcelain grates are available through OEM supply and cost significantly less than full grate set replacement after structural rust damage.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a150a; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🔧 ZLINE vs European Brands — Service Differences</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">ZLINE owners occasionally compare their service experience to European luxury brands they've heard about. The key differences: ZLINE parts availability is excellent through US-based supply — no week-long waits for Italian or German components. ZLINE's 1-year (now expanded) warranty is US-based with reasonable service network access. ZLINE's component architecture is designed for standard US technician tooling, not European-specific equipment. From a repair perspective, ZLINE is one of the more straightforward luxury-adjacent brands to service in the LA market.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 — COMMON PROBLEMS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common ZLINE Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Burner Won't Ignite</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Ceramic igniter failure — either thermal cycling fatigue or coastal salt air corrosion. ZLINE's sealed burner design requires OEM igniter geometry for correct spark alignment. Generic igniters provide weak or intermittent spark. We check recall status first — some ZLINE igniter failures are covered under active recalls. If not a recall item, OEM igniter replacement resolves most no-light conditions.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">⚠️ Recall-Related Gas Valve Fault</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Specific ZLINE range models have active recalls related to gas valve components. Symptoms vary by recall — some involve ignition issues, others involve gas control behavior during operation. We check CPSC and ZLINE recall database by model and serial number as the first step of every ZLINE service call. If your unit has an open recall, we'll direct you to the appropriate coverage channel.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-recall">Check Recall First</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Oven Temperature Off</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Temperature sensor drift or calibration offset — the oven runs consistently hot or cold by 15–30°F. We test with a calibrated probe at multiple setpoints before ordering parts. Many ZLINE oven temperature complaints are calibration-only (adjustable through the service menu) rather than sensor replacement. Calibration adjustment costs a fraction of sensor replacement.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🪨 Porcelain Grate Chipping + Rust</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Porcelain enamel chips at impact (dropped utensil, heavy pan contact) exposing bare cast iron. In coastal LA, salt air reaches the exposed iron within weeks and begins rust formation. Unlike bare cast iron grates (which can be re-seasoned), porcelain grates need replacement once the chip exposes significant metal area. We document chip locations and assess structural integrity on every ZLINE range call.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-grate">Porcelain Grate</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💨 Range Hood Blower Motor Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">ZLINE range hood blower motor — the most common hood failure across all brands and configurations. The motor degrades gradually: noise increases before it stops completely. We carry ZLINE hood blower assemblies in common CFM ratings on the truck. CFM-matched replacement is essential — wrong CFM creates either inadequate ventilation or excessive noise. We confirm CFM spec before ordering.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌊 Coastal Igniter Accelerated Corrosion</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Salt air corrosion on ZLINE ceramic igniter tips progresses faster than inland properties — typically 2–3 years at coastal properties vs 5–7 years inland. Properties in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Santa Monica, and Manhattan Beach should have igniter inspection every 2 years. We check all burner igniter tips on coastal ZLINE calls and replace proactively when corrosion is advanced.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-coastal">Coastal LA</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

